B. Dependency between scom and tsta
To show the dependencies between scom and tsta calculations for scom between 50m and 125m, acar = 10.4m/s² and vcar = 50km/h are done. The increase of tsta that can be achieved by increasing the radius of scom is also linearly dependent. This linear dependency can be seen in Fig. 7. The linear dependency is a result of the constant vcar with which the car covers distances larger than the braking distance, in our case here 9.725m.

